Why we are doing this study?

Problem: My favorite activity in the world is sleeping. Could I optimize it by controlling the different variables that might affect it?

Solution: Let’s dive into a sleeping study to discover which variables will improve or ruin a good night sleep!

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

gender_bar <- ggplot(data, aes(x=Gender, fill=Gender)) +
  geom_bar()

occup_bar <- ggplot(data, aes(x=Occupation, fill=Occupation)) +
  geom_bar() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1))

bmi_bar <- ggplot(data, aes(x=BMI.Category, fill=BMI.Category)) +
  geom_bar() 

blood_bar <- ggplot(data, aes(x=Blood.Pressure, fill=Blood.Pressure)) +
  geom_bar() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1))

sleep_bar <- ggplot(data, aes(x=Sleep.Disorder, fill=Sleep.Disorder)) +
  geom_bar()

gender_bar + bmi_bar 

occup_bar

blood_bar
